		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">jayminer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><img src="http://driar.se/pic/nes/shovelknight.png" alt="Image" /></div><br /><br />You -could- always overlays sprites on the Knight to make him look closer to the source game.  It seems like the Knight was the only thing that was left over from the &quot;let's make it look like an NES game as best as possible&quot; phase of development.  It'd be possible to recreate the game on the NES, you'd just need to re-arrange things (or remove them) to work.  One of the boss fights has a bunch of random NPCs just sitting there, so maybe they could be removed.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />That's cool, I think yours even looks a little better than the original.</div><br /><br />Even with it's flaws, I always thought the NES had a nice, vibrant palette.

		

